-- Assurant Obtains $130 Million of Catastrophe Bond Coverage
-- B y   A n d r e a   L u d t k e
-- 2012-01-31T21:35:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/assurant-obtains-130-million-of-catastrophe-bond-coverage.html
Assurant Inc. (AIZ) , the insurer of
foreclosed homes, obtained $130 million of natural-disaster
protection through catastrophe bonds.  The deal protects the company against losses from
hurricanes in  Hawaii ,  Puerto Rico  and the U.S. Gulf Coast and
East Coast, New York-based Assurant said today in a statement
distributed by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Ludtke in New York at 
 aludtke@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  